    "transcripts": [
      {
        "meeting_title": "AIOps Workshop Dry Run",
        "date": "2026-03-03T19:30:00.000Z",
        "doc_id": "doc_transcript_001",
        "doc_url": "https://docs.google.com/document/d/doc_transcript_001/edit",
        "participants": ["Jane Smith", "Alex Chen", "Pat Lee", "Ravi Patel"],
        "user_contributions": [
          {
            "timestamp": "0:02:15",
            "text": "So for the first lab exercise, I've restructured it to follow the new platform workflow. Instead of having participants manually create the inventory, they'll use the auto-discovery feature which is more realistic."
          },
          {
            "timestamp": "0:15:30",
            "text": "The main feedback from last cohort was that the networking section felt rushed. I've added an extra 20 minutes and split it into two exercises - basic network automation and then the advanced policy-as-code scenario."
          },
          {
            "timestamp": "0:28:45",
            "text": "For the demo environment, I'm proposing we use the new self-service provisioning. Each participant gets their own sandbox. I've already tested it with up to 30 concurrent users and it handles the load fine."
          }
        ],
        "total_lines": 342
      },
      {
        "meeting_title": "Globex Industries - AAP Demo",
        "date": "2026-03-04T21:00:00.000Z",
        "doc_id": "doc_transcript_002",
        "doc_url": "https://docs.google.com/document/d/doc_transcript_002/edit",
        "participants": ["Jane Smith", "Tom Rivera", "Lisa Park", "Mark Chen"],
        "user_contributions": [
          {
            "timestamp": "0:05:00",
            "text": "Thanks everyone for joining. Today I'll walk you through how Ansible Automation Platform can address the manual provisioning challenges you described. We'll look at three scenarios that map directly to your current workflow."
          },
          {
            "timestamp": "0:18:30",
            "text": "This workflow template is what handles the end-to-end server provisioning. Notice how it automatically runs the compliance checks after provisioning. Your team wouldn't need to manually trigger those separately."
          },
          {
            "timestamp": "0:35:12",
            "text": "Great question, Lisa. The role-based access control means your dev teams can self-service their own infrastructure requests without needing to go through a ticket queue. We've seen customers reduce their provisioning time from days to minutes."
          }
        ],
        "total_lines": 256
      }
    ]
